{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17510174","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17510174"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:25:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:25:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11501"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583481","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583481"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:16:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:16:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11501"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11501","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11501"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.24,0.04,0.14,0.09,0.49]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4132"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104635"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4132"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11501"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86983"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"492"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5695"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5138"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5169"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5532"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44843"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104635","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/104635"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 93-year-old female presents to the hospital in-patient unit for recurrent aspiration pneumonia on the background of late-stage dementia that was diagnosed 10 years ago. Over the past three months, her health has deteriorated significantly with multiple admissions due to sustained falls and aspiration pneumonia from her rapidly deteriorating cognition. The nursing staff also admitted that it has been difficult caring for her as she is now completely dependent on activities of daily living. Upon discussion with the ward doctors, the patient\u2019s family understood that end-of-life measures must be enacted given her deteriorating health. The patient previously made an Advance Care Directive (ACD) and appointed a substitute decision maker (SDM) when she had capacity.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"During periods when the patient is incapable of making her own decision, which one of the following decisions can a substitute decision-maker make?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Switching oral nutritional intake to tube feeding","Reducing the amount of palliative care medication i.e. pain analgesia","Finalising any legal or financial documentation","Request for voluntary euthanasia following patient\u2019s request","Choosing to transfer the patient into a hospice facility"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA substitute decision-maker (SDM) can be enacted within the Advance Care Directives. The role of an SDM is to make decisions for the patients about their health care, living arrangements and other personal matters when the patient is incapable of making their own decisions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, an SDM \u003Cstrong\u003Ecannot refuse food and water\u003C/strong\u003E to be given to the patient by mouth. The SDM also \u003Cstrong\u003Ecannot reduce medicine for pain\u003C/strong\u003E or distress i.e. pain analgesia. The SDM is also unable to make decisions about \u003Cstrong\u003Evoluntary euthanasia\u003C/strong\u003E in this case - even if the patient were to request it, as the question is posed in the setting of periods of decision-making incapacity. Legal advice should be sought as to the current state of assisted dying legislation in your state or territory and its application to this patient situation. SDM\u2019s are also \u003Cstrong\u003Eunable to make legal or financial decisions\u003C/strong\u003E i.e. changing the will of the patient unless the SDM is also the appointed Enduring Power of Attorney.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransferring the patient to a hospice facility \u003C/strong\u003Eis a decision to change her living arrangements, which is an appropriate decision an SDM can make.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The role of a substitute decision-maker under the Advance Care Directives is to make decisions for the patients about their health care, living arrangements and other personal matters when the patient is incapable of making their own decisions."],"references":["Advance Care Planning Australia [online]. 2022; accessed 2022 Jan 18. 2022. Available at: http://www.advancecareplanning.org.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86983"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11501"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86983","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86983"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-03T14:33:49+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-03T14:33:49